      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Jockey ANGEL CORDERO had his spleen removed yesterday and is in stable condition in the intensive care unit of Long Island Jewish Hospital, according to FRANK SANABRIA, the jockey's agent.</p>
        <p>The 49-year-old Cordero, who broke his left arm and three ribs, was the most seriously injured of four jockeys in a chain-reaction accident in the second-race at Aqueduct Sunday.</p>
        <p>SPORTS PEOPLE: HORSE RACING</p>
